# Dev dependencies = runtime + test tooling. Compiled (NO hashes) to requirements-dev.txt:
#   pip-compile requirements-dev.in -o requirements-dev.txt
# Note: a Windows compile includes pytest's win32-only `colorama` (pip-tools has no cross-platform
# marker mode); that line is a harmless no-op extra if you install on Linux. Hashes are omitted on
# purpose: Linux manylinux wheel hashes differ from the Windows win_amd64 hashes in
# requirements.txt, so --require-hashes can't be shared across platforms (PLAN.md).
-r requirements.in
pytest>=8
